63// Abstract base class for visiting, and optionally modifying, the
64// pointers contained in roots. Used in GC and serialization/deserialization.
65class RootVisitor {
66 public:
67 virtual ~RootVisitor() = default;
68
69 // Visits a contiguous arrays of pointers in the half-open range
70 // [start, end). Any or all of the values may be modified on return.
71 virtual void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
72 FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) = 0;
73
74 // Handy shorthand for visiting a single pointer.
75 virtual void VisitRootPointer(Root root, const char* description,
76 FullObjectSlot p) {
77 VisitRootPointers(root, description, p, p + 1);
78 }
79
80 // Visits a contiguous arrays of off-heap pointers in the half-open range
81 // [start, end). Any or all of the values may be modified on return.
82 //
83 // This should be implemented for any visitor that visits off-heap data
84 // structures, of which there are currently only two: the string table and the
85 // shared struct type registry. Visitors for those structures are limited in
86 // scope.
87 //
88 // If we ever add new off-heap data structures that we want to walk as roots
89 // using this function, we should make it generic, by
90 //
91 // 1) Making this function pure virtual, and
92 // 2) Implementing it for all visitors.
93 virtual void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
94 OffHeapObjectSlot start,
95 OffHeapObjectSlot end) {
96 UNREACHABLE();
97 }
98
99 // Visits a running Code object and potentially its associated
100 // InstructionStream from the execution stack.
101 virtual void VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot code_slot,
102 FullObjectSlot istream_or_smi_zero_slot) {
103 // For most visitors, currently running code is no different than any other
104 // on-stack pointer.
105 VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, istream_or_smi_zero_slot);
106 VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, code_slot);
107 }
108
109 // Intended for serialization/deserialization checking: insert, or
110 // check for the presence of, a tag at this position in the stream.
111 // Also used for marking up GC roots in heap snapshots.
112 virtual void Synchronize(VisitorSynchronization::SyncTag tag) {}
113
114 static const char* RootName(Root root);
115
116 // The type of collector that invokes this visitor. This is used by the
117 // ConservativeStackVisitor to determine which root pointers on the stack
118 // to follow, during conservative stack scanning. For MARK_COMPACTOR (the
119 // default) all pointers are followed, whereas for young generation
120 // collectors only pointers to objects in the young generation are followed.
121 virtual GarbageCollector collector() const {
122 return GarbageCollector::MARK_COMPACTOR;
123 }
124};

126class RelocIterator;

128// Abstract base class for visiting, and optionally modifying, the
129// pointers contained in Objects. Used in GC and serialization/deserialization.
130class ObjectVisitor {
131 public:
132 virtual ~ObjectVisitor() = default;
133
134 // Visits a contiguous arrays of pointers in the half-open range
135 // [start, end). Any or all of the values may be modified on return.
136 virtual void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot start,
137 ObjectSlot end) = 0;
138 virtual void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
139 MaybeObjectSlot end) = 0;
140 // When V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE is enabled, visits a InstructionStream pointer
141 // slot. The values may be modified on return. Not used when
142 // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE is not enabled (the InstructionStream pointer slots
143 // are visited as a part of on-heap slot visitation - via VisitPointers()).
144 virtual void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(Tagged<Code> host,
145 InstructionStreamSlot slot) = 0;
146
147 // Custom weak pointers must be ignored by the GC but not other
148 // visitors. They're used for e.g., lists that are recreated after GC. The
149 // default implementation treats them as strong pointers. Visitors who want to
150 // ignore them must override this function with empty.
151 virtual void VisitCustomWeakPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
152 ObjectSlot start, ObjectSlot end) {
153 VisitPointers(host, start, end);
154 }
155
156 // Handy shorthand for visiting a single pointer.
157 virtual void VisitPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot p) {
158 VisitPointers(host, p, p + 1);
159 }
160 virtual void VisitPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot p) {
161 VisitPointers(host, p, p + 1);
162 }
163 virtual void VisitCustomWeakPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot p) {
164 VisitCustomWeakPointers(host, p, p + 1);
165 }
166
167 virtual void VisitEphemeron(Tagged<HeapObject> host, int index,
168 ObjectSlot key, ObjectSlot value) {
169 VisitPointer(host, key);
170 VisitPointer(host, value);
171 }
172
173 // Visits the relocation info using the given iterator.
174 void VisitRelocInfo(Tagged<InstructionStream> host, RelocIterator* it);
175
176 virtual void VisitCodeTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
177 RelocInfo* rinfo) {}
178 virtual void VisitEmbeddedPointer(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
179 RelocInfo* rinfo) {}
180 virtual void VisitExternalReference(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
181 RelocInfo* rinfo) {}
182 virtual void VisitInternalReference(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
183 RelocInfo* rinfo) {}
184 // TODO(ishell): rename to VisitBuiltinEntry.
185 virtual void VisitOffHeapTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
186 RelocInfo* rinfo) {}
187
188 virtual void VisitExternalPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
189 ExternalPointerSlot slot) {}
190
191 // Same as `VisitExternalPointer` with the difference that the slot's contents
192 // are known to be managed by `CppHeap`.
193 virtual void VisitCppHeapPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
194 CppHeapPointerSlot slot) {}
195
196 virtual void VisitIndirectPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
197 IndirectPointerSlot slot,
198 IndirectPointerMode mode) {}
199
200 virtual void VisitProtectedPointer(Tagged<TrustedObject> host,
201 ProtectedPointerSlot slot) {}
202
203 virtual void VisitTrustedPointerTableEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
204 IndirectPointerSlot slot) {}
205
206 virtual void VisitMapPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host) { UNREACHABLE(); }
207};

209// Helper version of ObjectVisitor that also takes care of caching base values
210// of the main pointer compression cage and for the code cage.
211class ObjectVisitorWithCageBases : public ObjectVisitor {
212 public:
213 inline ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
214 PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base);
215 inline explicit ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(Isolate* isolate);
216 inline explicit ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(Heap* heap);
217
218 // The pointer compression cage base value used for decompression of all
219 // tagged values except references to InstructionStream objects.
220 PtrComprCageBase cage_base() const {
221#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
222 return cage_base_;
223#else
224 return PtrComprCageBase{};
225#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
226 }
227
228 // The pointer compression cage base value used for decompression of
229 // references to InstructionStream objects.
230 PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base() const {
231#ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
232 return code_cage_base_;
233#else
234 return cage_base();
235#endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
236 }
237
238 private:
239#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
240 const PtrComprCageBase cage_base_;
241#ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
242 const PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base_;
243#endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
244#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
245};

247// A wrapper class for root visitors that are used by client isolates during a
248// shared garbage collection. The wrapped visitor only visits heap objects in
249// the shared spaces and ignores everything else. The type parameter `Visitor`
250// should be a subclass of `RootVisitor`, or a similar class that provides the
251// required interface.
252template <typename Visitor = RootVisitor>
253class ClientRootVisitor final : public RootVisitor {
254 public:
255 explicit ClientRootVisitor(Visitor* actual_visitor)
256 : actual_visitor_(actual_visitor) {}
257
258 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
259 FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) final {
260 for (FullObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
261 Tagged<Object> object = *p;
262#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_LOCAL
263 if (object.ptr() == ValueHelper::kTaggedNullAddress) continue;
264#endif
265 if (!IsSharedHeapObject(object)) continue;
266 actual_visitor_->VisitRootPointer(root, description, p);
267 }
268 }
269
270 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
271 OffHeapObjectSlot start, OffHeapObjectSlot end) final {
272 actual_visitor_->VisitRootPointers(root, description, start, end);
273 }
274
275 inline void VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot code_slot,
276 FullObjectSlot maybe_istream_slot) final;
277
278 void Synchronize(VisitorSynchronization::SyncTag tag) final {
279 actual_visitor_->Synchronize(tag);
280 }
281
282 private:
283 V8_INLINE static bool IsSharedHeapObject(Tagged<Object> object) {
284 return IsHeapObject(object) &&
285 InWritableSharedSpace(HeapObject::cast(object));
286 }
287
288 Visitor* const actual_visitor_;
289};
290
291// A wrapper class for object visitors that are used by client isolates during a
292// shared garbage collection. The wrapped visitor only visits heap objects in
293// the shared spaces and ignores everything else. The type parameter `Visitor`
294// should be a subclass of `ObjectVisitorWithCageBases`, or a similar class that
295// provides the required interface.
296template <typename Visitor = ObjectVisitorWithCageBases>
297class ClientObjectVisitor final : public ObjectVisitorWithCageBases {
298 public:
299 explicit ClientObjectVisitor(Visitor* actual_visitor)
300 : ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(actual_visitor->cage_base(),
301 actual_visitor->code_cage_base()),
302 actual_visitor_(actual_visitor) {}
303
304 void VisitPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot p) final {
305 if (!IsSharedHeapObject(p.load(cage_base()))) return;
306 actual_visitor_->VisitPointer(host, p);
307 }
308
309 inline void VisitMapPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host) final;
310
311 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot start,
312 ObjectSlot end) final {
313 for (ObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
314 // The map slot should be handled in VisitMapPointer.
315 DCHECK_NE(host->map_slot(), p);
316 DCHECK(!HasWeakHeapObjectTag(p.load(cage_base())));
317 VisitPointer(host, p);
318 }
319 }
320
321 void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(Tagged<Code> host,
322 InstructionStreamSlot slot) final {
323#if DEBUG
324 Tagged<Object> istream_object = slot.load(code_cage_base());
325 Tagged<InstructionStream> istream;
326 if (istream_object.GetHeapObject(&istream)) {
327 DCHECK(!InWritableSharedSpace(istream));
328 }
329#endif
330 }
331
332 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
333 MaybeObjectSlot end) final {
334 // At the moment, custom roots cannot contain weak pointers.
335 UNREACHABLE();
336 }
337
338 inline void VisitCodeTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
339 RelocInfo* rinfo) final;
340
341 inline void VisitEmbeddedPointer(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
342 RelocInfo* rinfo) final;
343
344 private:
345 V8_INLINE static bool IsSharedHeapObject(Tagged<Object> object) {
346 return IsHeapObject(object) &&
347 InWritableSharedSpace(HeapObject::cast(object));
348 }
349
350 Visitor* const actual_visitor_;
351};
